<topic class="- topic/topic " id="unique_9" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="termic-motor-safety" oid="termic-motor-safety" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Steps to Ensure the Engine and Components are Safe to Work On</ph></title>
    <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">Follow these steps to ensure the termic (combustion) engine and its components are
        safe to work on before performing any maintenance.</shortdesc>
    <body class="- topic/body ">
        <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Turn Off the Engine:</b> Make sure the engine is completely turned off and the
                    key is removed from the ignition to prevent accidental starting.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Allow Engine to Cool:</b> Wait for the engine to cool down to avoid burns or
                    other injuries. This usually takes about 30 minutes after the engine has been
                    running.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Disconnect the Battery:</b> Disconnect the negative terminal of the car
                    battery to cut off the power supply, reducing the risk of electrical shocks.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Use Personal Protective Equipment (PPE):</b> Wear appropriate PPE such as
                    gloves, safety glasses, and long sleeves to protect yourself from potential
                    hazards.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Work in a Well-Ventilated Area:</b> Ensure you are working in an area with
                    good ventilation to avoid inhaling any harmful fumes or gases.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Secure the Vehicle:</b> Use wheel chocks to prevent the car from moving.
                    Engage the parking brake and ensure the vehicle is on a flat, stable
                    surface.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Refer to the Manual:</b> Always consult the vehicle's service manual for
                    specific safety instructions related to the termic motor.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </body>
